{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"4ec92cab-abd6-4659-a238-b10f64735656","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/git-transport-auth/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/git-transport-auth/spec.md","title":"credential.helper= per-invocation override not specified in fetch scenario","rationale":"The 'fetch succeeds without ambient git credentials' scenario only mentions http.<origin>.extraheader injection; it omits the credential.helper= empty override (design D2) that prevents headless hangs. An implementer could satisfy the scenario without adding the credential.helper override."},{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/git-transport-auth/spec.md","title":"base64-encoded token not explicitly excluded from log scenario","rationale":"The 'transport failure log excludes the token' scenario checks that the token does not appear in plaintext but does not mention base64-encoded form. Design D5 explicitly calls out base64 as reversible and therefore prohibited, but this is not reflected in the spec scenario, leaving a gap for test authors."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/git-transport-auth/spec.md","title":"Process-args token visibility not acknowledged as accepted risk in spec","rationale":"The base64 token is transiently visible in ps/proc during git invocation. This is accepted in design.md Risks but spec.md has no corresponding note, risking re-escalation in future reviews."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/git-transport-auth/tasks.md","title":"wrapTransportGitExecSpawn SpawnFn type comment is ambiguous","rationale":"T-01 uses SpawnFn for both util/spawn (async) and util/git-exec (sync, ChildProcess-returning) wrappers under the same identifier, which could cause implementer confusion. A distinct type alias name would clarify the distinction."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-11T02:18:11.345Z","endedAt":"2026-06-11T02:20:12.757Z"}
