{"type":"step-attempt","step":"code-review","sessionId":"9b64697f-94a2-403c-b427-2caf769fe4c5","outcome":{"verdict":"needs-fix","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/git-transport-auth/review-feedback-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":false,"findings":[{"severity":"high","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/git/__tests__/transport-auth.test.ts","title":"Wiring integration tests absent (TC-015, TC-016, TC-022 — must-priority)","rationale":"tasks.md T-07 marks wiring tests as done, but no test in any file verifies that LocalRuntime C1 fetch (`this.wrappedSpawnFn`), StepExecutor C5 pushOnly (`deps.gitTransportSpawn`), or archive orchestrator C8 main push (`transportAuth.wrapSpawn(input.spawn)`) actually inject auth args into the git invocations. A future refactor could silently disconnect the wiring with no failing test."},{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/git/transport-auth.ts","title":"HTTPS scope uses url.hostname (no port) — GHES non-standard port auth fails","rationale":"Scope is derived with `url.hostname` which omits the port. For GHES on a non-standard port (e.g., https://github.corp.com:8443/), the scope becomes https://github.corp.com/ and git's http.<url>.extraheader prefix-match does not match the actual URL. Auth injection silently degrades to no-auth while credential.helper= is still disabled, causing transport failure. Fix: use url.host which includes the port only when non-default.","line":61},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/git/transport-auth.ts","title":"Rejected Promise memoized in createTransportAuth — subsequent authArgs() calls fail","rationale":"If a caller-injected resolveOriginUrl throws, resolvePromise is set to a rejected Promise and never cleared. All subsequent authArgs() calls return the same rejected Promise. Harmless in production (default getRawOriginUrl never throws), but test resolvers that throw will see unexpected propagation across calls.","line":183}],"fixableCount":3},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-11T02:41:33.998Z","endedAt":"2026-06-11T02:49:27.450Z"}
